Package: mermaid-collab-server
Version: __VERSION__
Architecture: amd64
Maintainer: JLP Engineering <bmaderazo@jlpengineering.com>
Installed-Size: __INSTALLED_SIZE__
Depends: systemd, tmux, git, curl
Recommends: bun
Section: devel
Priority: optional
Homepage: https://github.com/ben-mad-jlp/claude-mermaid-collab
Description: Mermaid Collab headless sidecar (Electron-free)
 The compiled Bun mc-server sidecar plus a systemd user unit and the P0
 take-over-or-refuse port handshake. This is the headless / server install:
 it brings the collab API + orchestrator/worker session layer up on :9002
 with no Electron and no bun-on-PATH dependency (the binary is self-contained).
 .
 The mermaid-collab-desktop package depends on this one and adds the Electron
 GUI shell on top.
